{
  "rule": "vertical_remap",
  "applicable": false,
  "skip_reason": "vertical_remap is structurally a phase-hook operation (Lagrangian → Eulerian re-gridding between timesteps), not a §7 stencil rule. It has a variable-arity, data-dependent neighbor list (cumulative-pressure overlap of dp_old with dp_new) and binds time-varying per-column metrics that the §7 stencil schema does not encode. ESS will introduce a phase_hooks / integration_callbacks schema block in a future RFC; until then this rule is documentation-only and excluded from walker layer-B / layer-D execution. The rule's JSON file documents the math + AST shape as a reference artifact for the eventual phase-hook contract. There is no imperative implementation in any binding (Julia/Python/Rust/TypeScript) and none is to be re-added — see ESD/dsc-otd. Models needing a Lagrangian vertical configuration must use an Eulerian-vertical configuration today (e.g. centered_2nd_uniform_vertical) or wait for the phase-hook RFC."
}
